items.name: Nazrin (Touhou)
items.description:
Image posts are highly appreciated! You don't even need to leave a review. I just love to see what people are creating with my stuff.

Prompt nazrindef for default outfit.

Prompt nazrinrnd for "random" non-default clothing. (eg, nude, gym uniform, t-shirt, etc.)

Nazrin, the mouse youkai from the Touhou game series. I didn't realize until after I started pruning images from the dataset that the way Touhou characters look is extremely up to the interpretation of the artist. Various hair colors, various eye colors, and various colors and style of ear. So I found a base image that fit the way I felt she should look and pruned the training data until only fitting images remained. If you can't tell by the preview images, this means red eyes, light grey/whitish hair, and inwardly curved mouse ears with pink insides. The images rejected for the dataset had hair that was black, brown, brownish grey, dark grey, or pure white. Eyes that were brown, grey, purple, or pink. And ears that were either perfectly round circles, or that were inwardly curving but were grey/brown on the inside. So if you're expecting your Nazrin images to look like any of that, you're going to need to turn down the lora strength and add extra prompts for any specific colors/styles. Or try and find a different LoRA that's not trained to be as specific as this one.

As is standard with AI generation currently, getting the tail to generate properly is a game of luck. That, or inpainting if you can be bothered to learn.

Training workflow heavily based on Numeratic's character LoRA guide.

Ever feel like something is weighing you down? -1 out of 10 experts say it might be something in your wallet. Stop on down at Ko-Fi and find out today!

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

If you enjoyed this model, why don't you check out my other works? I put a lot of effort into correctly recreating artist styles and making the occasional character LoRA.😊

There already exist other LoRAs for this style on civitai and huggingface. I recommend that you compare them yourself, check the recommendations below.

I attempted to make this model consistent. No random monochrome images, broken anatomy or fragmented/panelled outputs.

About the artist:

Pixiv Fanbox: spray and pray - pixiv

Twitter: ratatatat74 (@ratatatat74) / Twitter

Patreon: Ratatatat74 | Creating painting | Patreon

Ratatatat74 is in large part a hentai artist, so you can expect the occassional nudity even when not specifically prompted. Their unique comic style is defined by often rough and angular linework and limited color palletes accentuated by strong shading.

For the more detailed art there is a general shine to the characters and women are almost always blushing.

Finally, a large part of their content is fanart with characters from MHA (Mirko in particular) and LoL

Weights & Prompts

pruned:

This should be your goto model if you do not want sketch style art.

Use a weight of .8-1.2. I just used 1.0. Adjust to taste and depending on your checkpoint.

Check the XYZ plot for reference.

Note that the activation prompt for this version is just:

ratatatat74

Because of the smaller dataset you can also expect a pretty consistent representation of Mirko with the right prompts. Try:

 long hair, large breasts, animal ears, white hair, thighs,  dark skin,  rabbit ears,  dark-skinned female, parted bangs,  muscular,  rabbit girl, muscular female, long eyelashes

The example images are almost exclusively redone images of the former versions for easy comparison - with some small changes to get the originally intended result.

For the other two versions the only necessary prompt is 

ratatatat74_style

although it mostly gets there even without prompts.

NAI:

Use a weight of 1.0, adjust to taste.

AOM:

Use a weight of 1.0, adjust to taste. This model is really flexible and is compatible with other LoRA (character or pose models) at full weight. As usual I have included an XYZ plot.

For inspiration check the examples. I heavily recommend experimenting with the steps as well. Sometimes a 12 step image is just what you want, sometimes it takes 30 to get the necessary detail.

It might be worth experimenting with some stylistic prompts that are baked in. Some possible options are

sketch, lineart

items.name: Lady Gaga (2008-2014)
items.description:
If you enjoy my models and want to help support my releases, I always need a coffee!

Here is my first releasable version of my first Gaga model, built completely from her look from 2008-2014, which SD has a difficult time with due to her "current" look permeating all models. This will definitely need some future refinement, and I'll also make a 2015-present version in the future but wanted to get this one out first. Please experiment and post results so that I can know what to adjust for future training. (I may also do album-by-album era loras at some point if there's enough interest)

Please don't use "lady gaga" in your prompt or rename the Lora file to include anything with "gaga" if you want to produce accurate results! After a lot of experimentation, the token "gaga" is extremely baked in all of the models to produce her "current" look. Therefore, it will always bleed into your results if you use it, even in the LoRA name. The tag to use is "gggg".

  • This was specfically trained to produce her Fame/Fame Monster/Born This Way/ARTPOP era look

  • I recommend using hires fix/MultiDuffusion/ADetailer to fix face problems

  • This LoRA stacks well on almost all models I've tried, from photorealistic to anime

  • Works best between 0.7-1.0

  • Please reference my posted generations for prompts, none have been retouched or inpainted, but I ran some of them through hires fix

  • Closeups generate far better than full body shots

  • It wants her mouth to be open and gives her funky teeth, use "closed mouth" in positive prompts or "teeth" in negatives to reduce the effect

  • She tends to not wear clothing even though I only used SFW data. Use nsfw, nude, breasts, etc in negative prompts to keep her clothes on

Please don't rip this off as your own, or do anything crazy with it. I am not releasing it for professional or commercial use, this is just for personal use and non-commercial research purposes. Please respect Gaga. And please share your results!

items.name: Jack Nicholson (Old) Lora
items.description:
Out with the young, in with the old!

Be nice, have fun!

John Joseph Nicholson (born April 22, 1937) is a retired American actor and filmmaker.[1] He is widely regarded as one of the greatest actors of all time.[2][3] In many of his films, he played rebels against the social structure.[4] He received numerous accolades throughout his five-decade-spanning career, including three Academy Awards, three BAFTA Awards, six Golden Globe Awards, a Grammy Award, and a Screen Actors Guild Award. He also received the American Film Institute's Life Achievement Award in 1994 and the Kennedy Center Honor in 2001.

Nicholson has won three Academy Awards, for Best Actor for One Flew Over the Cuckoo's Nest (1975) and As Good as It Gets (1997) and for Best Supporting Actor for Terms of Endearment (1983). He was Oscar-nominated for Easy Rider (1969), Five Easy Pieces (1970), The Last Detail (1974), Chinatown (1974), Reds (1981), Prizzi's Honor (1986), Ironweed (1987), A Few Good Men (1992) and About Schmidt (2002). Nicholson is also known for his notable roles in Carnal Knowledge (1971), The Shining (1980), Heartburn (1986), Broadcast News (1987), Batman (1989), Hoffa (1992), Mars Attacks! (1996), Something's Gotta Give (2003), The Departed (2006) and The Bucket List (2007).

Nicholson has directed three films, Drive, He Said (1971), Goin' South (1978), and The Two Jakes (1990). He is one of only three male actors to win three Academy Awards, and one of only two actors to be nominated for an Academy Award for acting in films made in every decade from the 1960s to the 2000s. His 12 Academy Award nominations make Nicholson the most nominated male actor in the Academy's history.

items.description:
The Voynich Manuscript is a mysterious document, handwritten in a unique and undeciphered script, dating from the early 15th Century. The Manuscript has defied all efforts at translation by linguists, historians, alchemists, lawyers, and NSA cryptographers. The text's author is unknown, with a list of possible candidates including English polymath Francis Bacon, and a youthful Leonardo da Vinci (using his non-dominant right hand). Theories on the text's original purpose include a health manual, a recipe book, an elaborate hoax, directions to the Fountain of Youth, an astrological almanac, and coded instructions from time-travelling extraterrestrials on how to create DNA using sound.

This LoRA has been trained on original pages from the Voynich Manuscript. While it is unlikely to unlock the Manuscript's secrets, it can certainly help you generate some mysteries of your own.

items.name: Fortuny
items.description:
This Lora generates images of the iconic Delphos gown created by Mariano Fortuny. From wikipedia: "Fortuny rebelled against the style lines that were popular during his time period, and he and Henriette created the Delphos gown,[8] a shift dress made of finely pleated silk weighed down by glass beads that held its shape and flowed on the body. The pleating that he used was all done by hand and no one has been able to recreate pleating that is as fine as his[citation needed] or has held its shape like his dresses have for many years." Mariano Fortuny (designer) - Wikipedia

I love this design. It is a unique look that is timeless. Use the Lora at full strength otherwise you will lose some of the finer details.

The Delphos gown

By Mariano Fortuny y Madrazo - Museo del Traje, CC BY-SA 4.0, https://commons.wikimedia.org/w/index.php?curid=46087802

Note the short sleeves, the micro-pleated silk and the row of glass beads that weighs down the fabric at the seams. Distinctive features are the boat neck and the longer than floor length hem so it puddles on the floor. It can be worn with or without the matching belt. Have fun.
